cs.DM, cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.GT, cs.CC

The paper deals with algorithmic problems on graphs that model interval relations, which is a topic that falls under discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The use of geometric representations and sweep line algorithms suggests that computational geometry (cs.CG) is also relevant. The dominating set problem is a classic problem in graph theory (cs.DS) and the paper specifically addresses this problem on tolerance and multitolerance graphs. The study of graph theory and optimization problems is also related to game theory (cs.GT) and complexity theory (cs.CC).
